column1:
['	For endorsements,

	    		If the Affinity is deleted, the Affinity Origination Code is set to Blank.
	
	    		If the number of days between Policy Inception date and Endorsement Effective Date is greater than 30 days then Origination Code is set to "E".
	
	    		If the number of days between Policy Inception date and Endorsement Effective Date is less than 30 days that is if the Affinity is added before 30 days then the Origination Code is set to "N".
	
	    		For New Business, If it is a Primary Policy of MRP or Secondary Policy of MRP,
	
	    		If the Multiple Record Policy Code is not "S" and If secondary policy in MRP has affinity relationship associated, then the Affinity Origination Code of the linked policy is set with the values that are already present in the associated policy.
	
	    		If secondary policy in MRP does not have affinity relationship associated then Affinity Card Number, Affinity Origination Code and Affinity Relation Codes of the linked policy are set with the values that are already present in the associated policy.
	
	    		If the Multiple Record Policy Code is "S"- If the affinity relationship is associated with the policy then Affinity Origination Code of the linked policy is set with the value that is already present in the policy.
	
	    		If the affinity relationship is not associated with the policy then Affinity Card Number, Affinity Origination Code and Affinity Relation Codes of the linked policy are set with the values that are already present in the associated policy.']

      If the age of the driver is less than 25 years and if the marital status of the driver is valid,
      If Smart Student discount proof is neither received nor validated then set smart student code to "A". Else set the smart student code to Empty Space (" ").
']

column1: ["The Primary Insured's Last Name cannot be left blanks."]

['For New Business,

     Driver age is derived based on the below two attributes.

     1.  Driver birth date.
     2. Effective date.

For Endorsement,

     For all states, Driver age is derived based on the below two attributes.

     1.  Driver birth date.
     2. Endorsement Effective date.

\xa0

However, in states MI, MN, NJ, SC, CA, TX and SRM 6 states, for existing drivers, the driver age is derived based on below two attributes

     1. Driver birth date.
     2. Policy term effective date

If the existing driver on a policy was added on a date which is greater than term effective date, the driver age is derived from\xa0Driver birth date and\xa0Endorsement Effective date when one of the below conditions are met.

     Calculated driver age is greater than the term effective age (derived from the {LINK id=143381 title="Age Calculation" uri=https://jazz.allstate.com:9443/rm/resources/_qLDvMe0HEeWFUsLd0XjL1w})
     Rating state is MI, MN, NJ, SC, CA, TX and any SRM 6 state. 

Note:\xa0\xa0Refer to the\xa0{LINK id=141769 title="SRM Phase Values" uri=https://jazz.allstate.com:9443/rm/resources/_A0TvDuXsEeWgyLn4fbTY2w}\xa0for the list of SRM 6 states.
']

column1:
['Young Driver Flag will not be set\xa0to C\xa0when number of years licensed is less than 5.
Young Driver Flag will be set to D when number of years licensed is above 5 and below 10.
Young Driver Flag will be set to D when number of years licensed is greater than 10 and less than 20.
By default, Young Driver Flag is set to E (E – represents Number of years licensed greater or equal to 9).
This rule is not applicable for the SBO Types-Cancel Rewrite ,Re-instatement,TransferIn,Spinoff,Splitoff,TransferIn.']
